# Content Quality Rules — applies to all city pages, current and future

---

## RULE 1 — Link reliability

A link is only useful if it reliably takes the user somewhere helpful.

### Keep a link if it is:
- A stable root homepage (`https://www.idealista.com`)
- A stable official government or institutional page (`https://icp.gov.ae`, `https://aima.gov.pt`)
- A stable school or hospital website root (`https://www.apis.ac.th`)
- A Facebook **group** URL with a slug (`https://www.facebook.com/groups/chiangmaiexpatclub`) — groups with named slugs are stable
- A Numbeo cost-of-living page — these are stable reference URLs

### Replace with fallback text if it is:
- Missing entirely — use `"label": "Search '[name]' on Google"`
- A Facebook **search** URL (`facebook.com/search/…`) — unstable, requires login
- A deep filtered/search-result URL from a rental portal
- A government PDF or press release (not a stable page)
- A link to a company that may not exist or has been rebranded
- An empty `url` field (`""`)

### Fallback format by section:

```json
// Schools — no stable URL
{ "name": "School Name", "curriculum": "IB", "fees": "$X,000 / yr" }
// Do NOT add a url field. The renderer generates a Google search fallback automatically.

// Housing portal — no stable city page
{ "label": "DDproperty.com — search 'Chiang Mai'", "url": "https://www.ddproperty.com" }

// Facebook community
{ "label": "Search on Facebook: 'Group Name' — brief description of what it's for" }
// Do NOT add a url field for Facebook search guidance.

// Visa — no stable official link
// Omit the officialLink field entirely. The details[] content is the action.
```

