## RULE 2 — Jargon dictionary (always explain inline on first use)

When a jargon term appears in any section, explain it inline in the same sentence on first use.
Format: `"[TERM] ([plain English explanation])"`

### Spain / Portugal

| Term | Plain explanation |
|---|---|
| Padrón / Padrón Municipal | Spain's official address register |
| NIE | Spanish foreigner ID number |
| TIE | Spain's physical residency card |
| Ayuntamiento | city hall |
| Extranjería | local immigration office |
| SIP | Spain's free public healthcare registration card |
| guardería | nursery / daycare (Spanish) |
| cuidadora | nanny (Spanish) |
| NIF | Portugal's combined tax and ID number |
| Junta de Freguesia | Portugal's local civil registry office |
| Finanças | Portugal's tax office |
| AIMA | Portugal's immigration authority |
| SNS | Portugal's free national health system |
| NHR | Portugal's Non-Habitual Resident tax scheme — reduces foreign income tax to 20% for 10 years |
| creche | nursery (Portuguese) |

### UAE / Dubai

| Term | Plain explanation |
|---|---|
| Emirates ID | UAE's national identity card — required for banking, healthcare, and school enrolment |
| EJARI | Dubai's mandatory tenancy registration system — your legal protection as a tenant |
| KHDA | Dubai's official nursery and school quality regulator |
| GDRFA | Dubai's General Directorate of Residency and Foreigners Affairs — handles residency visas |
| ICP | UAE's Federal Authority for Identity, Citizenship, Customs and Port Security — issues Emirates ID |

### Thailand

| Term | Plain explanation |
|---|---|
| TM30 | Address registration form that your landlord must file with immigration within 24 hours of your arrival |
| 90-day report | Required address check-in to Thai immigration every 90 days — can be done online |
| DTV | Destination Thailand Visa — 5-year multiple-entry visa for remote workers |
| moo ban | Thai term for a gated residential village |

### General

| Term | Plain explanation |
|---|---|
| Apostille | An official government certification that authenticates a document for use in another country |
| medevac | Medical evacuation — emergency transport to a higher-level hospital |
| IPMI | International Private Medical Insurance |
| IBAN | International Bank Account Number — required for international transfers |

